  ;; --- COMPONENT PLACEMENT & WIRING NOTES ---
  (text "=== LOWER PCB  rev 1.1  ===\n\nU1: Seeed XIAO ESP32-S3 (castellated module)\n     GPIO1->JOY_X, GPIO2->JOY_Y, GPIO3->JOY_SW\n     GPIO4->VBAT_SENSE\n     GPIO5->BTN_LEFT, GPIO6->BTN_RIGHT\n     GPIO7->BTN_BACK, GPIO8->BTN_FWD\n     GPIO19->USB_DN, GPIO20->USB_DP\n     3V3->3V3, GND->GND\n     USB-C end faces board edge (aligned with base ring cutout)\n     KEEPOUT: no copper within 3mm of antenna (module edge)\n\nU2: TP4056 (SOP-8) -- Near USB-C connector\n     VIN->VBUS, BAT->BAT+, GND->GND\n     PROG->R8(2k)->GND  (sets 500mA charge current)\n     CHRG->R9(1k)->LED1(RED)->GND\n     STDBY->R10(1k)->LED2(GRN)->GND\n\nU3: AP2112K-3.3V (SOT-23-5) -- Between battery and XIAO\n     VIN->switched BAT+ (via SW1), VOUT->3V3, GND->GND\n     CE->VIN (always enabled when power is on)\n\nU4: USBLC6-2SC6 (SOT-23-6) -- Next to J1\n     IO1->USB_DP, IO2->USB_DN, VBUS->VBUS, GND->GND\n\nJ1: USB-C receptacle (mid-mount) -- Board edge\n     VBUS, D+->USB_DP, D-->USB_DN, GND\n     CC1->R11(5.1k)->GND, CC2->R12(5.1k)->GND\n\nJ2: JST-PH 2-pin right-angle -- Battery connector\n     Pin1->BAT+, Pin2->GND\n\nJ3: FPC 6-pin 0.5mm top-contact -- Center of board\n     Cable routes upward through body shell to upper PCB J5\n     Pin1->3V3, Pin2->GND\n     Pin3->BTN_LEFT, Pin4->BTN_RIGHT\n     Pin5->BTN_BACK, Pin6->BTN_FWD\n     NOTE: BTN signals have pull-ups on upper PCB, NOT here\n\nJ4: 5-pin header 2.54mm right-angle -- Joystick module\n     Pin1->3V3, Pin2->GND\n     Pin3->JOY_X, Pin4->JOY_Y, Pin5->JOY_SW\n\nSW1: SPDT slide switch (MSK-12C02) -- Board edge\n     COM->BAT+, NO->U3 VIN  (master power)\n\nSW2: Tactile 3x4mm (BOOT) -- Near U1\n     U1 GPIO0->GND when pressed\n\nSW3: Tactile 3x4mm (RESET) -- Near U1\n     U1 EN->GND when pressed\n\nResistors:\n     R_PU5: 10k  3V3->JOY_SW  (joystick click pull-up)\n     R5:   100k  BAT+->VBAT_SENSE (voltage divider top)\n     R6:   100k  VBAT_SENSE->GND  (voltage divider bottom)\n     R7:     2k  TP4056 PROG->GND (charge current 500mA)\n     R8:     1k  TP4056 CHRG->LED1\n     R9:     1k  TP4056 STDBY->LED2\n     R10:  5.1k  USB-C CC1->GND\n     R11:  5.1k  USB-C CC2->GND\n     NOTE: BTN pull-ups R_PU1-R_PU4 REMOVED -- now on upper PCB as R1-R4\n\nDecoupling caps:\n     C1-C4: 100nF 0402 on 3V3 rail (one on each side of U1)\n     C5:    10uF  0805 bulk on 3V3\n     C6:    10uF  0805 on VBUS\n     C7:    10uF  0805 on BAT+\n\nLEDs:\n     LED1: Red 0402 -- charge indicator (on while charging)\n     LED2: Green 0402 -- standby indicator (on when full/idle)"
    (at 120 30 0)
    (uuid "00000001-0001-0001-0001-000000000099")
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left))
  )
